Results.description: The array of topSystems matching your request.

ucsdBackupInfo.title: Ucsd:Backup Info
ucsdBackupInfo.description: List of backup images available for target end device for restore operation.

BackupFileName.description: Auto generated backup File Name with combination of file prefix given an user input and the timestamp.

BackupLocation.description: Backup location that contains the backup images for end device which can be used for restore operation.

BackupServerIp.description: Backup server where backup images are maintained.

BackupSize.description: Size of the backup image in bytes.

Connectors.description: Connector pack versions that are active on the UCS Director when this backup image was taken.

Duration.description: Time taken for the backup to be completed.

EncryptionKey.description: The key used for encrypting the backup file.

IsPurged.description: Backup image got purged or not. The backup images get purged based on the retention count set by the user in the backup config policy.

LastModified.description: Last modified time when this backup record got updated.

PercentageCompletion.description: Backup current precentage completion status information.

ProductVersion.description: The end device product version when the backup image was taken.

Protocol.description: Protocol used for the remote backup. possible values are FTP, SCP and SFTP. Not applicable for the localhost (127.0.0.1).

StartTime.description: Start time of backup when it got initiated.

Status.description: Current status of Backup current.

Count.description: The number of ucsdBackupInfos matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of ucsdBackupInfos matching your request.

ucsdConnectorPack.title: Ucsd:Connector Pack
ucsdConnectorPack.description: Information about the connector packs present in the backup file.

ConnectorFeature.description: State of the connector pack whether it is enabled or disabled.

DependencyNames.description: List of dependent connectors on the UCS Director for this connector. For example BigData depends on UCS Connector.

DownloadedVersion.description: Version of the connector pack that is last downloaded successfully to UCS Director.

Name.description: Name of the connector pack running on the UCS Director.

Services.description: List of dependent connectors on the UCS Director for this connector. For example BigData depends on UCS Connector.

State.description: State of the connector pack whether it is enabled or disabled.

Version.description: Version of the connector pack.

ucsdUcsdRestoreParameters.title: Ucsd:Ucsd Restore Parameters
ucsdUcsdRestoreParameters.description: Restore Configuration Parameters for UCS Director restore workflow

Location.description: The complete location of the path on the server. The location should be specified in the following format- hostname-or-ipv4address<:port>/absolute-file-path.

Password.description: The password of the target backup server. Only required if the target server is accessed using SFTP or SCP protocol.

Protocol.description: The protocol used to backup the UCS Director.

RestoreConfigurationFiles.description: Decides whether UCS Director property files should also be restored.

RestoreLicense.description: Decides whether license should also be restored.

Username.description: The username of the target backup server. Only required if the target server is accessed using SFTP or SCP protocol.

viewsView.title: Views:View
viewsView.description: An abstract representation of a view. A view provides read-only access to the object model. A view can combine and transform data from multiple data sources.

virtualizationAbstractVirtualMachine.title: Virtualization:Abstract Virtual Machine
virtualizationAbstractVirtualMachine.description: Common attributes of a virtual machine managed by a  hypervisor. Serves as a base class for all concrete virtual machine types. A virtual machine (VM) is what a user and applications interact with. A VM usually runs a guest OS and applications run on the guest OS.

Capacity.description: Provisioned CPU and memory information for this virtual machine.

GuestInfo.description: Guest operating system details running on this machine.

HypervisorType.description: Type of hypervisor where the virtual machine is hosted, for example VMware ESXi.

Identity.description: The internally generated identity of this vm. This entity is not manipulated by users. It aids in uniquely identifying the virtual machine object. For VMware, this is MOR (managed object reference).

IpAddress.description: The ip address of the virtual machine. There could be multiple addresses of IPv4 and IPv6 types.

MemoryCapacity.description: The capacity and usage information for memory on this virtual machine.

Name.description: User-provided name to identify the virtual machine.

PowerState.description: Power state of the virtual machine.

ProcessorCapacity.description: The capacity and usage information for CPU power on this virtual machine.

Uuid.description: The uuid of this virtual machine. The uuid is internally generated and not user specified.

virtualizationCluster.title: Virtualization:Cluster
virtualizationCluster.description: Common attributes of a cluster of resources within a datacenter. A cluster is a convenient grouping of resources such as Host, Datastore, etc.

HypervisorType.description: Identifies the broad type of the underlying hypervisor.

Identity.description: The internally generated identity of this cluster. This entity is not manipulated by users. It aids in uniquely identifying the cluster object. In case of VMware, this is a MOR (managed object reference).

MemoryCapacity.description: The capacity and usage information for memory on this cluster.

Name.description: The user-provided name for this cluster to facilitate identification.

ProcessorCapacity.description: The capacity and usage information for CPU power on this cluster.

Status.description: Cluster health status as reported by the hypervisor platform.

TotalCores.description: Total number of CPU cores in this cluster. It is a cumulative number across all hosts in the cluster.

virtualizationComputeCapacity.title: Virtualization:Compute Capacity
virtualizationComputeCapacity.description: Details of available CPU power across all cores and the free capacity still available.

Capacity.description: Total capacity of the entity in MHz.

Free.description: Free CPU capacity in MHz, as a point-in-time snapshot. The available CPU capacity is reported for an entity (such as Host or Cluster) when inventory data is collected for that entity. As part of the inventory data, a snapshot of the free and used CPU capacity is also reported.

Used.description: Used CPU capacity of the entity in MHz, as a point-in-time snapshot.

virtualizationCpuInfo.title: Virtualization:Cpu Info
virtualizationCpuInfo.description: The details of the CPUs on this platform.

Cores.description: Number of cores per CPU, as reported by the manufacturer.

Description.description: The vendor provided description of the CPU (example:Intel Xeon E5-2640 v3 @ 2.60GHz).

Speed.description: Speed of the CPUs in Hertz (Hz, example 2593749663).

virtualizationDatacenter.title: Virtualization:Datacenter
virtualizationDatacenter.description: Common attributes of any datacenter. Serves as a base class for all concrete hypervisor types. Datacenter (DC) is the container that brings together all other elements (Host, Datastore, Virtual Machine) A typical DC has datastores for storage for Virtual Machines, and a handful of hosts to run the Virtual Machines. In addition, there could be virtual switches and portgroups in those switches.

Identity.description: Internally generated identity of this datacenter. This entity is not manipulated by users. It aids in uniquely identifying the datacenter object. For VMware, this is a MOR (managed object reference).

Name.description: User provided name for the datacenter. Usually, this name is subject to manipulations by user. It is not the identity of the datacenter.

virtualizationDatastore.title: Virtualization:Datastore
virtualizationDatastore.description: Common attributes of a datastore allocated to a hypervisor. Serves as a base class for all concrete datastore types. A datastore is assigned to a datacenter and virtual machines use it for storage. The datastore could be backed by NFS, VMFS, etc.

HostCount.description: Number of hosts attached to or supported-by this datastore.

Identity.description: The internally generated identity of this datastore. This entity is not manipulated by users. It aids in uniquely identifying the datastore object. For VMware, this is a MOR (managed object reference).

Name.description: Name of this datastore supplied by user. It is not the identity of the datastore. The name is subject to user manipulations.

Type.description: A string indicating the type of the datastore (VMFS, NFS, etc).

VmCount.description: Number of virtual machines relying on (using) this datastore.

virtualizationGuestInfo.title: Virtualization:Guest Info
virtualizationGuestInfo.description: Captures the common details of the guest personality that runs in a VM.

Hostname.description: Name provided to the host OS (example, ubuntu6410, test-gateway, etc.).

IpAddress.description: Primary ip address of the guest os.

Name.description: The name of the guest running on this VM. This may not be the same as the host name.

OperatingSystem.description: The name of the guest OS running on this VM (Cent OS 4/5/6/7).

virtualizationHost.title: Virtualization:Host
virtualizationHost.description: Common attributes of any host associated to a hypervisor manager. Serves as a base class for all concrete host types A Host belongs to a datacenter and optionally to a cluster, and runs virtual machines on it. A host is basically a hardware platform that runs the VMs. Depending on the capacity of the host, it can support 100s of virtual machines.

CpuInfo.description: Details about the CPUs installed on this host are represented here.

HardwareInfo.description: The hardware details of this host. It includes capacity, manufacturer, and model information.

HypervisorType.description: Identifies the broad type of the underlying hypervisor.

Identity.description: The internally generated identity of this host. This entity is not manipulated by users. It aids in uniquely identifying the datacenter object. For VMware, this is an MOR (managed object reference).

MaintenanceMode.description: Is this host in maintenance mode. Set to true or false.

MemoryCapacity.description: The memory capacity and usage information on this host.

Model.description: Commercial model information about this hardware.

Name.description: Name of this host supplied by user. It is not the identity of the host. The name is subject to user manipulations.

ProcessorCapacity.description: The capacity and usage information for CPU power on this host.

ProductInfo.description: Details of this product, such as vendor, model, etc. are represented here.

Serial.description: Serial number of this host (internally generated).

Status.description: Host health status, as reported by the hypervisor platform.

UpTime.description: The uptime of the host, stored as Duration (from w3c).

Uuid.description: Universally unique identity of this host (example b3d4483b-5560-9342-8309-b486c9236610). Internally generated.

Vendor.description: Commercial vendor details of this hardware.

virtualizationHypervisorManager.title: Virtualization:Hypervisor Manager
virtualizationHypervisorManager.description: The basic hypervisor manager. Serves as a management layer for all hypervisors. A hypervisor manager contains datacenters, and datacenters contain all other entities such as Host, Portgroups, Virtual Machines, etc.

Identity.description: Identity of the hypervisor (not manipulated by user). It could be a UUID too. Example - c917093f-5443-4748-bc09-eec72ded7608.

Name.description: The user provided name for the hypervisor manager (for example, vCenterIreland). Usually, this name is subject to manipulations by user. It is not the identity of the hypervisor.

Version.description: Release version of the Hypervisor Manger (VMware vCenter Server 6.0.0 build-4541947).

RegisteredDevice.description: Every inventory object comes from a device endpoint. The identity of that device is captured here so that any entity that needs to send a request to that device can just get to it via the inventory object.

virtualizationMemoryCapacity.title: Virtualization:Memory Capacity
virtualizationMemoryCapacity.description: Measure of memory allocated and used.

Capacity.description: The total memory capacity of the entity in bytes.

Free.description: Free memory (bytes) that is unused and available for allocation, as a point-in-time snapshot. The available memory capacity is reported for an entity (such as Host or Cluster) when inventory data is collected for that entity. As part of the inventory data, a snapshot of the free and used memory capacity is also reported.

Used.description: Memory (bytes) that has been already used up, as a point-in-time snapshot.

virtualizationProductInfo.title: Virtualization:Product Info
virtualizationProductInfo.description: The details of the product offering.

ProductName.description: Commercial product name, example, VMware ESXi.

ProductType.description: Indication of product type by the vendor, example, embeddedEsx.

ProductVendor.description: Commercial vendor name, example, VMware, Inc'.

Version.description: Hypervisor version running on the system.

virtualizationRemoteDisplayInfo.title: Virtualization:Remote Display Info
virtualizationRemoteDisplayInfo.description: Details of the remote display settings.

RemoteDisplayPassword.description: The password used for remote access. It is stored base64 encoded.

RemoteDisplayVncKey.description: The access key for the remote display, potentially a long string.

RemoteDisplayVncPort.description: Applies only when remoteDisplayvnc is enabled.

virtualizationResourceConsumption.title: Virtualization:Resource Consumption
virtualizationResourceConsumption.description: Stats on the resources consumed by this host.

CpuConsumed.description: The amount of CPU consumed in Hz.

MemoryConsumed.description: Memory consumed by this host in bytes.

virtualizationSourceDevice.title: Virtualization:Source Device
virtualizationSourceDevice.description: Every inventory object comes from a device endpoint. The identity of that device is captured here so that any entity that needs to send a request to that device can just get to it via the inventory object.

RegisteredDevice.description: Every inventory object comes from a device endpoint. The identity of that device is captured here so that any entity that needs to send a request to that device can just get to it via the inventory object.

virtualizationStorageCapacity.title: Virtualization:Storage Capacity
virtualizationStorageCapacity.description: Captures the common attributes of a storage entity.

Capacity.description: The total capacity of the entity (bytes).

Free.description: Free storage space remaining in the entity (bytes) as a point-in-time snapshot. The available space is reported for an entity (such as Host or Cluster) when inventory data is collected for that entity. As part of the inventory data, a snapshot of the free and used storage capacity is also reported.

Used.description: Spaced already used by this entity (bytes), as a point-in-time snapshot.

virtualizationVmCpuShareInfo.title: Virtualization:Vm Cpu Share Info
virtualizationVmCpuShareInfo.description: Information about the virtual machine's CPU sharing and limits.

CpuOverheadLimit.description: Amount of CPU for virtualization overhead.

CpuReservation.description: Guaranteed minimum allocation of CPU resource (MHz).

CpuShares.description: Good description found in VMware docs. Basically, indicates the relative importance of a vm. There is no unit for this value. It is a relative measure based on the settings for other resource pools.

virtualizationVmCpuSocketInfo.title: Virtualization:Vm Cpu Socket Info
virtualizationVmCpuSocketInfo.description: Information about the virtual machine's hardware platform (CPU, memory).

CoresPerSocket.description: Need to say more? This value may be empty.

NumCpus.description: Number of CPUs allocated to this vm.

NumSockets.description: The number of CPU sockets allocated.

virtualizationVmDiskCommitInfo.title: Virtualization:Vm Disk Commit Info
virtualizationVmDiskCommitInfo.description: Information about the virtual machine's disk commits, sharing and limits (details in VMware docs).

CommittedDisk.description: Disk committed in bytes on this virtual machine (disk space used up).

UnCommittedDisk.description: Total uncommited disk space that is available for use (in bytes).

virtualizationVmMemoryShareInfo.title: Virtualization:Vm Memory Share Info
virtualizationVmMemoryShareInfo.description: Information about the virtual machine's memory sharing and limits (details in VMware docs).

MemLimit.description: Limit on the memory sharing imposed (in Mbytes).

MemOverheadLimit.description: Limit on memory overhead imposed (in Mbytes).

MemShares.description: Similar to cpuShares but applicable to memory. There is no unit for this value. It is a relative measure based on the settings for other resource pools.

virtualizationVmwareCluster.title: Virtualization:Vmware Cluster
virtualizationVmwareCluster.description: A real cluster of resources within a data center in VMware. A cluster is a convenient grouping of resources such as Host, Datastore, etc.

DatastoreCount.description: Count of all datastores associated with this cluster.

Datacenter.description: Every entity is grouped under the datacenter object and managed as a group.

Hosts.description:
A collection of references to the [virtualization.VmwareHost](mo://virtualization.VmwareHost) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [virtualization.VmwareHost](mo://virtualization.VmwareHost) MOs unset their reference to this deleted MO.

Count.description: The number of virtualizationVmwareClusters matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of virtualizationVmwareClusters matching your request.

virtualizationVmwareDatacenter.title: Virtualization:Vmware Datacenter
virtualizationVmwareDatacenter.description: Datacenter object in VMware inventory. It is the logical container for all other objects like Datastore, Host, VirtualMachine, etc.

ClusterCount.description: Count of all clusters associated with this DC.

DatastoreCount.description: Count of all datastores associated with this DC.

HostCount.description: Count of all hosts associated with this DC.

NetworkCount.description: Count of all networks associated with this datacenter (DC).

VmCount.description: Count of all virtual machines (VMs) associated with this DC.

HypervisorManager.description: Hypervisor to which this datacenter belongs. All entities are owned by the hypervisor.

Count.description: The number of virtualizationVmwareDatacenters matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of virtualizationVmwareDatacenters matching your request.

virtualizationVmwareDatastore.title: Virtualization:Vmware Datastore
virtualizationVmwareDatastore.description: The VMware Datastore entity with its attributes. Every Datastore belongs to a Datacenter and maybe attached to VMs.

Accessible.description: Indicates if this datastore is accessible.

MaintenanceMode.description: Is the datastore in maintenance mode. Will be set to true when in maintenance mode.

MultipleHostAccess.description: Is this datastore connected to multiple hosts.

Status.description: Datastore health status, as reported by the hypervisor platform.

ThinProvisioningSupported.description: Does this datastore support thin provisioning for files.

UnCommitted.description: Space uncommitted in this datastore in bytes.

Url.description: The URL to access this datastore (example - 'ds:///vmfs/volumes/562a4e8a-0eeb5372-dd61-78baf9cb9afa/').

Cluster.description: Specifies cluster associated with the datastore entity. Not every datastore is in a cluster and therefore this relation may not exist.

Datacenter.description: Every entity is grouped under the datacenter object and managed as a group.

Hosts.description: The list of hosts that are attached to this host. Used for the new inventory model and will soon replace hostList above.

Count.description: The number of virtualizationVmwareDatastores matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of virtualizationVmwareDatastores matching your request.

virtualizationVmwareHost.title: Virtualization:Vmware Host
virtualizationVmwareHost.description: The VMware Host entity with its attributes. Every Host belongs to a Datacenter and probably runs VMs.

BootTime.description: It is the time when this host booted up.

ConnectionState.description: Is host connected to vCenter. Values are connected, notconnected.

HwPowerState.description: Is the host powered-up or powered-down.

NetworkAdapterCount.description: It is the count of all network adapters attached to this host.

ResourceConsumed.description: Snapshot of resources (CPU, memory, etc.) consumed by this host.

StorageAdapterCount.description: It is the count of all storage adapters attached to this host.

VcenterHostId.description: The identity of this host within vCenter (optional).

Cluster.description: Specifies associated cluster with the host entity. It is optional and upto platform to decide.

Datacenter.description: Every entity is grouped under the datacenter object and managed as a group.

Datastores.description:
A collection of references to the [virtualization.VmwareDatastore](mo://virtualization.VmwareDatastore) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [virtualization.VmwareDatastore](mo://virtualization.VmwareDatastore) MOs unset their reference to this deleted MO.

Count.description: The number of virtualizationVmwareHosts matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of virtualizationVmwareHosts matching your request.

virtualizationVmwareVcenter.title: Virtualization:Vmware Vcenter
virtualizationVmwareVcenter.description: VMware vCenter entity. The vCenter has a name assigned by user in Intersight.

Count.description: The number of virtualizationVmwareVcenters matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of virtualizationVmwareVcenters matching your request.

virtualizationVmwareVirtualMachine.title: Virtualization:Vmware Virtual Machine
virtualizationVmwareVirtualMachine.description: The VMware Virtual machine. It has details such as power state, IP address, resource consumption, etc. Basic elements come from the base class and VMware specific details are provided here.

Annotation.description: List of annotations provided to this VM by user; Can be long.

BootTime.description: Time when this vm booted up.

ConfigName.description: The named config for this vm, might be the same as guestHostname.

ConnectionState.description: Is virtual machine connected to vCenter. Values are connected, disconnected, orphaned, inaccessible, invalid.

CpuHotAddEnabled.description: Is the capability to add CPUs to a running VM enabled.

CpuShares.description: Basically, indicates the relative importance of a vm and its CPU limits.

CpuSocketInfo.description: Details of CPUs/sockets of this vm.

CustomAttributes.description: User provided meta information associated with VMs. Can be long.

DefaultPowerOffType.description: Indication of how the VM will be powered off (soft, hard, etc).

DhcpEnabled.description: Is Dhcp used for IP/DNS on this vm.

DiskCommitInfo.description: Information about the virtual machine's disk commits, sharing and limits.

DnsServerList.description: List of DNS server IPs assigned to this VM.

DnsSuffixList.description: List of dnssuffixes given to this VM.

Folder.description: The folder name associated with this VM.

GuestState.description: State of the guest OS on this VM. Is it running, notRunning, etc.

InstanceUuid.description: UUID assigned by vCenter to every VM.

IsTemplate.description: If true, indicates that the entity refers to a template of a virtual machine and not a real virtual machine.

MacAddress.description: Standard MAC address assigned to this VM.

MemShares.description: Similar to cpuShares but applicable to memory.

MemoryHotAddEnabled.description: Adding memory to a running VM.

NetworkCount.description: How many networks are used by this VM.

PortGroups.description: List of portgroup names allocated to this vm.

ProtectedVm.description: Is this a protected VM. VMs can be in protection groups.

RemoteDisplayInfo.description: Applies only when remoteDisplayvnc is enabled.

RemoteDisplayVncEnabled.description: Is support for a remote VNC access enabled.

ResourcePool.description: Name of the resource pool to which this vm belongs (optional).

ResourcePoolParent.description: The parent of the current resource pool to which this VM belongs.

ToolRunningStatus.description: Are guest tools running on this vm. Set to (guestToolNotRunning,  guestToolsRunning).

ToolsVersion.description: The version of the guest tools, usually not specified.

VmDiskCount.description: How many disks are assigned to this VM.

VmOverallStatus.description: The operational state (there are many possible states, Available, Provisioned, Maintenance mode, Deleting, etc.) of this vm.

VmVersion.description: Information about the version of this VM (vmx-09, vmx-11 etc.).

VnicDeviceConfigId.description: Information related to the guest info's vnic virtual device (this is a comma separated list).

Cluster.description: If the virtual machine is running on a cluster, it provides associated cluster information.

Datacenter.description: Every entity is grouped under the datacenter object and managed as a group.

Datastores.description: The list of datastores that are attached to this VM. Used for the new inventory model and will soon replace dataStoreList above.

Host.description: Host on which the Virtual Machine resides.

Count.description: The number of virtualizationVmwareVirtualMachines matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of virtualizationVmwareVirtualMachines matching your request.

vmediaMapping.title: Vmedia:Mapping
vmediaMapping.description: Virtual Media mapping settings required to map images from remote server.

AuthenticationProtocol.description: Type of Authentication protocol when CIFS is used for communication with the remote server.

DeviceType.description: Type of remote Virtual Media device.

HostName.description: IP address or hostname of the remote server.

MountOptions.description:
Mount options for the Virtual Media mapping. The field can be left blank or filled in a comma separated list with the following options.
 For NFS, supported options are ro, rw, nolock, noexec, soft, port=VALUE, timeo=VALUE, retry=VALUE.
 For CIFS, supported options are soft, nounix, noserverino, guest.
 For HTTP/HTTPS, the only supported option is noauto.

MountProtocol.description: Protocol to use to communicate with the remote server.

Password.description: Password associated with the username.

RemoteFile.description: Name of the remote file. It should be of .img format for HDD Virtual Media mapping and .iso format for CDD Virtual Media mapping.

RemotePath.description: URL path to the location of the image on the remote server. The preferred format is '/path/'.

Username.description: Username to log in to the remote server.

VolumeName.description: Identity of the image for Virtual Media mapping.

vmediaPolicy.title: Virtual Media
vmediaPolicy.description: Policy to configure virtual media settings on endpoint.

Enabled.description: State of the Virtual Media service on the endpoint.

Encryption.description: If enabled, allows encryption of all Virtual Media communications.

LowPowerUsb.description: If enabled, the virtual drives appear on the boot selection menu after mapping the image and rebooting the host.

Mappings.description: Adds a new Virtual Media mapping for images.

Organization.description: Relationship to the Organization that owns the Managed Object.

Count.description: The number of vmediaPolicies matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of vmediaPolicies matching your request.

vnicArfsSettings.title: ARFS Settings
vnicArfsSettings.description: Settings for Accelerated Receive Flow Steering to reduce the network latency and increase CPU cache efficiency.

Enabled.description: Status of Accelerated Receive Flow Steering on the virtual ethernet interface.

vnicCdn.title: Consistent Device Naming
vnicCdn.description: Consistent Device Naming configuration for the virtual NIC.

Source.description: Source of the CDN. It can either be user specified or be the same as the vNIC name.

Value.description: The CDN value entered in case of user defined mode.

Count.description: The number of completion queue resources to allocate. In general, the number of completion queue resources you should allocate is equal to the number of transmit queue resources plus the number of receive queue resources.

RingSize.description: The number of descriptors in each completion queue.

vnicEthAdapterPolicy.title: Ethernet Adapter
vnicEthAdapterPolicy.description: An Ethernet adapter policy governs the host-side behavior of the adapter, including how the adapter handles traffic. For each VIC Virtual Ethernet Interface you can configure various features like VXLAN, NVGRE, ARFS, Interrupt settings, and TCP Offload settings.

AdvancedFilter.description: Enables advanced filtering on the interface.

ArfsSettings.description: Settings for Accelerated Receive Flow Steering to reduce the network latency and increase CPU cache efficiency.

InterruptSettings.description: Interrupt Settings for the virtual ethernet interface.

NvgreSettings.description: Network Virtualization using Generic Routing Encapsulation Settings.

RoceSettings.description: Settings for RDMA over Converged Ethernet.

RssSettings.description: Receive Side Scaling allows the incoming traffic to be spread across multiple CPU cores.

TcpOffloadSettings.description: The TCP offload settings decide whether to offload the TCP related network functions from the CPU to the network hardware or not.

Organization.description: Relationship to the Organization that owns the Managed Object.

Count.description: The number of vnicEthAdapterPolicies matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of vnicEthAdapterPolicies matching your request.

Cdn.description: Consistent Device Naming configuration for the virtual NIC.

Name.description: Name of the virtual ethernet interface.

Order.description: The order in which the virtual interface is brought up. The order assigned to an interface should be unique for all the Ethernet and Fibre-Channel interfaces on each PCI link on a VIC adapter. The maximum value of PCI order is limited by the number of virtual interfaces (Ethernet and Fibre-Channel) on each PCI link on a VIC adapter. All VIC adapters have a single PCI link except VIC 1385 which has two.

Placement.description: Placement Settings for the virtual interface.

UsnicSettings.description: User Space NIC Settings that enable low-latency and higher throughput by bypassing the kernel layer when sending/receiving packets.

VmqSettings.description: Virtual Machine Queue Settings for the virtual interface that allow efficient transfer of network traffic to the guest OS.

EthAdapterPolicy.description: Relationship to the the Ethernet Adapter Policy.

EthNetworkPolicy.description: Relationship to the Ethernet Network Policy.

EthQosPolicy.description: Relationship to the Ethernet QoS Policy.

LanConnectivityPolicy.description: Relationship to the LAN Connectivity Policy.

Organization.description: Relationship to the Organization that owns the Managed Object.

Results.description: The array of vnicEthIfs matching your request.

vnicEthInterruptSettings.title: Interrupt Settings
vnicEthInterruptSettings.description: Interrupt settings for the virtual ethernet interface.

CoalescingTime.description: The time to wait between interrupts or the idle period that must be encountered before an interrupt is sent. To turn off interrupt coalescing, enter 0 (zero) in this field.

CoalescingType.description: Interrupt Coalescing Type. This can be one of the following:- MIN  - The system waits for the time specified in the Coalescing Time field before sending another interrupt event IDLE - The system does not send an interrupt until there is a period of no activity lasting as least as long as the time specified in the Coalescing Time field.

Count.description: The number of interrupt resources to allocate. Typical value is be equal to the number of completion queue resources.

Mode.description: Preferred driver interrupt mode. This can be one of the following:- MSIx - Message Signaled Interrupts (MSI) with the optional extension. MSI  - MSI only. INTx - PCI INTx interrupts. MSIx is the recommended option.

vnicEthNetworkPolicy.title: Ethernet Network
vnicEthNetworkPolicy.description: An Ethernet Network policy determines if the port can carry single VLAN (Access) or multiple VLANs (Trunk) traffic. You can specify the VLAN to be associated with an Ethernet packet if no tag is found.

VlanSettings.description: VLAN configuration for the virtual interface.

Organization.description: Relationship to the Organization that owns the Managed Object.

vnicEthQosPolicy.title: Ethernet QoS
vnicEthQosPolicy.description: An Ethernet Quality of Service (QoS) policy assigns a system class to the outgoing traffic for a vNIC. This system class determines the quality of service for the outgoing traffic. For certain adapters you can also specify additional controls like burst and rate on the outgoing traffic.

Cos.description: Class of Service to be associated to the traffic on the virtual interface.

Mtu.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) or packet size that the virtual interface accepts.

RateLimit.description: The value in Mbps (0-100000) to use for limiting the data rate on the virtual interface. Setting this to zero will turn rate limiting off.

TrustHostCos.description: Enables usage of the Class of Service provided by the operating system.

vnicFcAdapterPolicy.title: Fibre Channel Adapter
vnicFcAdapterPolicy.description: A Fibre Channel Adapter policy governs the host-side behavior of the adapter, including how the adapter handles traffic. You can enable FCP Error Recovery, change the default settings of Queues and Interrupt handling for performance enhancement.

ErrorDetectionTimeout.description: Error Detection Timeout, also referred to as EDTOV, is the number of milliseconds to wait before the system assumes that an error has occurred.

InterruptSettings.description: Interrupt Settings for the virtual fibre channel interface.

IoThrottleCount.description: The maximum number of data or control I/O operations that can be pending for the virtual interface at one time. If this value is exceeded, the additional I/O operations wait in the queue until the number of pending I/O operations decreases and the additional operations can be processed.

LunCount.description: The maximum number of LUNs that the Fibre Channel driver will export or show. The maximum number of LUNs is usually controlled by the operating system running on the server.

LunQueueDepth.description: The number of commands that the HBA can send and receive in a single transmission per LUN.

ResourceAllocationTimeout.description: Resource Allocation Timeout, also referred to as RATOV, is the number of milliseconds to wait before the system assumes that a resource cannot be properly allocated.

Organization.description: Relationship to the Organization that owns the Managed Object.

Results.description: The array of vnicFcAdapterPolicies matching your request.

Enabled.description: Enables Fibre Channel Error recovery.

IoRetryCount.description: The number of times an I/O request to a port is retried because the port is busy before the system decides the port is unavailable.

IoRetryTimeout.description: The number of seconds the adapter waits before aborting the pending command and resending the same IO request.

LinkDownTimeout.description: The number of milliseconds the port should actually be down before it is marked down and fabric connectivity is lost.

PortDownTimeout.description: The number of milliseconds a remote Fibre Channel port should be offline before informing the SCSI upper layer that the port is unavailable. For a server with a VIC adapter running ESXi, the recommended value is 10000. For a server with a port used to boot a Windows OS from the SAN, the recommended value is 5000 milliseconds.

Name.description: Name of the virtual fibre channel interface.

Order.description: The order in which the virtual interface is brought up. The maximum value of PCI order is limited by the number of virtual interfaces (Ethernet and Fibre-Channel) on each PCI link on a VIC adapter. All VIC adapters have a single PCI link except VIC 1385 which has two.

PersistentBindings.description: Enables retention of LUN ID associations in memory until they are manually cleared.

Placement.description: Placement Settings for the virtual interface.

FcAdapterPolicy.description: Relationship to the the Fibre Channel Adapter Policy.

FcNetworkPolicy.description: Relationship to the Fibre Channel Network Policy.

FcQosPolicy.description: Relationship to the Fibre Channel QoS Policy.

vnicFcInterruptSettings.description: Interrupt Settings for the virtual fibre channel interface.

vnicFcNetworkPolicy.description: A Fibre Channel Network policy governs the VSAN configuration for the virtual interfaces.

VsanSettings.description: VSAN configuration for the virtual interface.

vnicLanConnectivityPolicy.title: LAN Connectivity
vnicLanConnectivityPolicy.description: A LAN Connectivity Policy determines the network resources and the connections between the server and the LAN on the network. This policy uses Consistent Device Naming to configure the vNIC. You can configure a usNIC or VMQ connection for the vNIC to improve network performance.

vnicNvgreSettings.title: NVGRE Settings
vnicNvgreSettings.description: Network Virtualization using Generic Routing Encapsulation Settings.

Enabled.description: Status of the Network Virtualization using Generic Routing Encapsulation on the virtual ethernet interface.

vnicPlacementSettings.title: Placement Settings
vnicPlacementSettings.description: Placement Settings for the virtual interface.

Id.description: PCIe Slot where the VIC adapter is installed. Supported values are (1-15) and MLOM.

PciLink.description: The PCI Link used as transport for the virtual interface. All VIC adapters have a single PCI link except VIC 1385 which has two.

Uplink.description: Adapter port on which the virtual interface will be created.

Retries.description: The number of times that the system tries to log in to a port after the first failure.

Timeout.description: The number of milliseconds that the system waits before it tries to log in again.

vnicRoceSettings.title: RoCE Settings
vnicRoceSettings.description: Settings for RDMA over Converged Ethernet.

Enabled.description: If enabled sets RDMA over Converged Ethernet (RoCE) on this virtual interface.

MemoryRegions.description: The number of memory regions per adapter. Recommended value = integer power of 2.

QueuePairs.description: The number of queue pairs per adapter. Recommended value = integer power of 2.

ResourceGroups.description: The number of resource groups per adapter. Recommended value = be an integer power of 2 greater than or equal to the number of CPU cores on the system for optimum performance.

vnicSanConnectivityPolicy.title: SAN Connectivity
vnicSanConnectivityPolicy.description: SAN connectivity policy determines the network storage resources and the connections between the server and the SAN on the network. This policy enables you to configure vHBAs that the servers use to communicate with the storage network.

FcIfs.description:
A collection of references to the [vnic.FcIf](mo://vnic.FcIf) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [vnic.FcIf](mo://vnic.FcIf) MOs on the other side of the relationship are deleted.
