RingSize.description: The number of descriptors in each SCSI I/O queue.

vnicTcpOffloadSettings.title: TCP Offload
vnicTcpOffloadSettings.description: The TCP offload settings decide whether to offload the TCP related network functions from the CPU to the network hardware or not. These options help reduce the CPU overhead and increase the network throughput.

LargeReceive.description: Enables the reassembly of segmented packets in hardware before sending them to the CPU.

LargeSend.description: Enables the CPU to send large packets to the hardware for segmentation.

RxChecksum.description: When enabled, the CPU sends all packet checksums to the hardware for validation.

TxChecksum.description: When enabled, the CPU sends all packets to the hardware so that the checksum can be calculated.

vnicUsnicSettings.title: USNIC Settings
vnicUsnicSettings.description: User Space NIC Settings that enable low-latency and higher throughput by bypassing the kernel layer when sending/receiving packets.

Cos.description: Class of Service to be used for traffic on the usNIC.

Count.description: Number of usNIC interfaces to be created.

UsnicAdapterPolicy.description: Ethernet Adapter policy to be associated with the usNICs.

vnicVlanSettings.title: VLAN Settings
vnicVlanSettings.description: VLAN configuration for the virtual interface.

DefaultVlan.description: Default VLAN ID of the virtual interface. Setting the ID to 0 will not associate any default VLAN to the traffic on the virtual interface.

Mode.description: Option to determine if the port can carry single VLAN (Access) or multiple VLANs (Trunk) traffic.

vnicVmqSettings.title: VMQ Settings
vnicVmqSettings.description: Virtual Machine Queue Settings for the virtual interface that allow efficient transfer of network traffic to the guest OS.

Enabled.description: Enables VMQ feature on the virtual interface.

vnicVsanSettings.title: VSAN Settings
vnicVsanSettings.description: VSAN configuration for the virtual interface.

Id.description: Default VSAN ID of the virtual interface. Setting the ID to 0 will not associate any default VSAN to the traffic on the virtual interface.

Enabled.description: Status of the Virtual Extensible LAN Protocol on the virtual ethernet interface.

workflowAbstractWorkerTask.title: Workflow:Abstract Worker Task
workflowAbstractWorkerTask.description: An AbstractWorkerTask is used to model a task that does some end-user work. This can be another task or it can be another workflow.

InputParameters.description: JSON formatted map that defines the input given to the task. JSONPath is used for chaining output from previous tasks as inputs into the current task. The format to specify the mapping is '${Source.input/output.JsonPath}'. 'Source' can be either workflow or the name of the task within the workflow. You can map the task input to either a workflow input or a task output. Following this is JSON path expression to extract JSON fragment from source's input/output.

OnFailure.description: This specifies the name of the next task to run if Task fails.  This is the unique name given to the task instance within the workflow. In a graph model, denotes an edge to another Task Node.

OnSuccess.description: This specifies the name of the next task to run if Task succeeds.  This is the unique name given to the task instance within the workflow. In a graph model, denotes an edge to another Task Node.

workflowApi.title: API
workflowApi.description:
Intersight Orchestrator supports generic API workflow tasks that can execute
an API given the request body and response parser specification.
API type models a single API request within a batch of requests that get
executed within a single workflow task.

Body.description:
The optional request body that is sent as part of this API request.
The request body can contain a golang template that can be populated with task input
parameters and previous API output parameters.

ContentType.description:
Intersight Orchestrator, with the support of response parser specification,
can extract the values from API responses and map them to task output parameters.
The value extraction is supported for response content types XML and JSON.
The type of the content that gets passed as payload and response in this
API.

Name.description:
A reference name for this API request within the batch API request.
This name shall be used to map the API output parameters to subsequent
API input parameters within a batch API task.

Outcomes.description:
All the possible outcomes of this API are captured here. Outcomes property
is a collection property of type workflow.Outcome objects.
The outcomes can be mapped to the message to be shown. The outcomes are
evaluated in the order they are given. At the end of the outcomes list,
an catchall success/fail outcome can be added with condition as 'true'.
This is an optional
property and if not specified the task will be marked as success.

ResponseSpec.description:
The optional grammar specification for parsing the response to extract the
required values.
The specification should have extraction specification specified for
all the API output parameters.

SkipOnCondition.description:
The skip expression, if provided, allows the batch API executor to skip the
api execution when the given expression evaluates to true.
The expression is given as such a golang template that has to be
evaluated to a final content true/false. The expression is an optional and in
case not provided, the API will always be executed.

Timeout.description:
The duration in seconds by which the API response is expected from the API target.
If the end point does not respond for the API request within this timeout
duration, the task will be marked as failed.

workflowArrayDataType.title: Workflow:Array Data Type
workflowArrayDataType.description: This data type represents an array of a given type. It can be an array of primitive data or of custom data.

ArrayItemType.description: Data item within the array data type.

Max.description: Specify the maximum value of the array.

Min.description: Specify the minimum value of the array.

workflowArrayItem.title: Workflow:Array Item
workflowArrayItem.description: ArrayItem represents an array item within the array.

workflowBaseDataType.title: Workflow:Base Data Type
workflowBaseDataType.description: The base data type that is used to derive all the other data types for inputs and outputs.

Default.description: Default value for the data type. If default value was provided and the input was required the default value will be used as the input.

Description.description: Provide a detailed description of the data type.

Label.description: Descriptive label for the data type. Name can only contain letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), hyphen (-), space ( ) or an underscore (_). The first and last character in label must be an alphanumeric character.

Name.description: Descriptive name for the data type. Name can only contain letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), hyphen (-) or an underscore (_). The first and last character in name must be an alphanumeric character.

Required.description: Specifies whether this parameter is required. The field is applicable for task and workflow.

workflowBatchApiExecutor.title: Batch API
workflowBatchApiExecutor.description:
Intersight allows generic API tasks to be created by taking the API request
body and a response parser specification in the form of content.Grammar object.
Batch API associates the list of API requests to be executed as part of single
task execution. Each API request takes the request body and a response parser
specification.

Batch.description:
Intersight Orchestrator supports one or a batch of APIs to be executed as part of
a task execution.
The batch cannot be empty.

Constraints.description: Enter the constraints on when this task should match against the task definition.

Description.description: A detailed description about the batch APIs.

Name.description: Name for the batch API task.

Outcomes.description:
All the possible outcomes of this task are captured here. Outcomes property
is a collection property of type workflow.Outcome objects.
The outcomes can be mapped to the message to be shown. The outcomes are
evaluated in the order they are given. At the end of the outcomes list,
an catchall success/fail outcome can be added with condition as 'true'.
This is an optional
property and if not specified the task will be marked as success.

Output.description:
Intersight Orchestrator allows the extraction of required values from API
responses using the API response grammar. These extracted values can be mapped
to task output parameters defined in task definition.
The mapping of API output parameters to the task output parameters is provided
as JSON in this property.

SkipOnCondition.description:
The skip expression, if provided, allows the batch API executor to skip the
task execution when the given expression evaluates to true.
The expression is given as such a golang template that has to be
evaluated to a final content true/false. The expression is an optional and in
case not provided, the API will always be executed.

TaskDefinition.description: The interface task definition for which this batch API is one of the implementation.

Count.description: The number of workflowBatchApiExecutors matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowBatchApiExecutors matching your request.

workflowBuildTaskMeta.title: Workflow:Build Task Meta
workflowBuildTaskMeta.description: Contains relationship for tasks within a workflow. It is used to dynamically generate a workflow.

Name.description: Name for the BuildTaskMeta instance used to created a dynamic workflow.

Src.description: Microservice owner for the task in this workflow.

TaskList.description: Task list used to build the dynamic workflow.

TaskType.description: The type of the task within this workflow.

WorkflowType.description: The type for the dynamic workflow.

Count.description: The number of workflowBuildTaskMeta matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowBuildTaskMeta matching your request.

workflowBuildTaskMetaOwner.title: Workflow:Build Task Meta Owner
workflowBuildTaskMetaOwner.description: Contains the list of dynamic workflow types that a microservice supports.

Service.description: The microservice owner responsible for the tasks.

WorkflowTypes.description: The list of workflow types supported by the microservice.

Count.description: The number of workflowBuildTaskMetaOwners matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowBuildTaskMetaOwners matching your request.

workflowCatalog.title: Workflow:Catalog
workflowCatalog.description:
A catalog of workflow related objects such as workflow and task definitions. Each user account will have a local workflow catalog where account users can store their private workflow and task definitions.
Cisco provides validated workflows and tasks to Intersight users via shared catalogs. Intersight users will be able to read, run these workflows and tasks within their account context. The shared catalogs will be managed entirely by Cisco. Contributions to shared catalogs will need to be provided to Cisco who will publish them at their own discretion.

Name.description: A unique name for the catalog.

Organization.description: Relationship to the Organization that owns the Managed Object.

Count.description: The number of workflowCatalogs matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowCatalogs matching your request.

workflowCliCommand.title: CLI Command
workflowCliCommand.description: This models a single CLI command that can be executed on the end point.

Command.description: The command to run on the device connector.

EndPrompt.description: The regex string that identifies the end of the command response.

ExpectPrompts.description:
Cli prompts required as part of interactive command execution. For e.g. login credentials will be part of prompts
which are provided as list of expect prompt regex and corresponding answer string.

SkipStatusCheck.description:
Skips the execution status check of the terminal command. One use case for this is while exiting the
terminal session from esxi host.

TerminalEnd.description: If this flag is set, it marks the end of the terminal session where the previous commands were executed.

TerminalStart.description:
If this flag is set, the execution of this command initiates a terminal session in which the subsequent
CLI commands are executed until a command with terminalEnd flag is encountered or the end of the batch.

Type.description: The type of the command - can be interactive or non-interactive.

workflowConstraints.title: Workflow:Constraints
workflowConstraints.description: Captures the constraints for valid parameter values.

EnumList.description: When the parameter is a enum then this list of enum entry is used to validate the input belongs to one of items in the list.

Max.description: Allowed maximum value of the parameter if parameter is integer/float or maximum length of the parameter if the parameter is string. When max and min are set to 0, then the limits are not checked.

Min.description: Allowed minimum value of the parameter if parameter is integer/float or minimum length of the parameter if the parameter is string. When max and min are set to 0, then the limits are not checked.

Regex.description: When the parameter is a string this regular expression is used to ensure the value is valid.

workflowControlTask.title: Workflow:Control Task
workflowControlTask.description: Control tasks run within the workflow engine and are not executed by remote worker microservices. They are used to modify flow of control within a workflow.

workflowCustomDataProperty.title: Workflow:Custom Data Property
workflowCustomDataProperty.description: Capture all the properties for Custom data type.

CatalogMoid.description: Specify the catalog moid that this custom data type belongs.

CustomDataTypeId.description: The resolved custom data type definition managed object.

CustomDataTypeName.description: Name of the custom data type for this input.

workflowCustomDataType.title: Workflow:Custom Data Type
workflowCustomDataType.description: This data type represents a custom data object.

Properties.description: Captures the custom data type properties.

workflowCustomDataTypeDefinition.title: Custom Datatype
workflowCustomDataTypeDefinition.description: Captures a customized data type definition that can be used for task or workflow input/output.  This can be reused across multiple tasks and workflow definitions.

CompositeType.description: When true this data type definition is a collection of type definitions to represent composite data like JSON.

Description.description: A human-friendly description of this custom data type indicating it's domain and usage.

Label.description: A user friendly short name to identify the custom data type definition.

Name.description: The name of custom data type definition. The valid name can contain lower case and upper case alphabetic characters, degits and special characters '-' and '_'.

TypeDefinition.description: The properties of this custom data type definition.

Catalog.description: The catalog under which the definition is present.

Count.description: The number of workflowCustomDataTypeDefinitions matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowCustomDataTypeDefinitions matching your request.

workflowDecisionCase.title: Workflow:Decision Case
workflowDecisionCase.description: A Decision Case is a condition for a Decision Task. It is the equivalent of case statement in the programming language paradigm of switch and case.

Description.description: Description of this decision case.

NextTask.description: The name of the next task (Task names unique within workflow) to run.  In a graph model, denotes an edge to another Task Node.

workflowDecisionTask.title: Workflow:Decision Task
workflowDecisionTask.description: A DecisionTask is a control task that executes a sequence of WorkflowTasks based off decision provided and evaluated by this task.

Condition.description: The condition to evaluate for this decision task. The condition can be a workflow or task variable or an expression based on the input parameters. Example value for condition if its Workflow/task variable is -  "${task1.output.var1} or ${workflow.input.var2}" which evaluates to a value matching any of the decision case values. Example value for condition if its an expression is - "if ( $.element ! = null && $.element > 0 ) 'true'; else 'false'; " which evaluates to 'true' or 'false' and will match one of the decision case values. Here "element" is a variable in decisiontask's inputParameters JSON formatted map. You can also use javascript like functions indexOf, toUpperCase in the expression which will be evaluated by the expression evaluator.

DecisionCases.description: A list of potential decision task flows based off a condition.

DefaultTask.description: The default next Task to execute if the decision cannot be evaluated to any of the DecisionCases.

InputParameters.description: JSON formatted map that defines the input given to the decision task. The inputs are used as variables in the condition property of decision task. The input variables can be static values like "hello" , "24", "true" OR previous task outputs/workflow inputs like "${task2.output.var1}}". The input variables are referrenced as $.inputVariableName in the condition property.

workflowDefaultValue.title: Workflow:Default Value
workflowDefaultValue.description: Captures default vales for a data type.

Override.description: Override the default value provided for the data type. When true, allow the user to enter value for the data type.

Value.description: Default value for the data type. If default value was provided and the input was required the default value will be used as the input.

workflowDynamicWorkflowActionTaskList.title: Workflow:Dynamic Workflow Action Task List
workflowDynamicWorkflowActionTaskList.description: Keeps a list of the tasks to add for a corresponding workflow action when PendingDynamicWorkflowInfo is built.

Action.description: The action of the Dynamic Workflow.

Tasks.description: The task list that has precedence which dictates how the workflow should be constructed.

workflowEndTask.title: Workflow:End Task
workflowEndTask.description: An EndTask denotes the completion of a workflow.

workflowEnumEntry.title: Workflow:Enum Entry
workflowEnumEntry.description: Captures a single enum entry which has a label and value.

Label.description: Label for the enum value. A user friendly short string to identify the enum value.

Value.description: Enum value for this enum entry. Value will be passed to the workflow as string type for execution.

workflowExpectPrompt.title: Expect Prompt
workflowExpectPrompt.description: This models a single expect and answer prompt of the interactive command.

Expect.description: The regex of the expect prompt of the interactive command.

Send.description: The answer string to the expect prompt.

workflowFailureEndTask.title: Workflow:Failure End Task
workflowFailureEndTask.description: A FailureEndTask denotes the failed completion of a workflow.

workflowInternalProperties.title: Workflow:Internal Properties
workflowInternalProperties.description: Internal properties for a task definition which are not editable by the user.

BaseTaskType.description: This field will hold the base task type like HttpBaseTask or RemoteAnsibleBaseTask.

Constraints.description: This field will hold any constraints a concrete task definition will specify in order to limit the environment where the task can execute.

Internal.description: Denotes this is an internal task. Internal tasks will be hidden from the UI when executing a workflow.

Owner.description: The service that owns and is responsible for execution of the task.

workflowMessage.title: Workflow:Message
workflowMessage.description: Intermediate Task or Workflow message with severity.

Message.description: An i18n message that can be translated in multiple languages to support internationalization.

Severity.description: The severity of the Task or Workflow message warning/error/info etc.

workflowMoReferenceDataType.title: Workflow:Mo Reference Data Type
workflowMoReferenceDataType.description: Data type to capture an Intersight Managed object reference.

workflowMoReferenceProperty.title: Workflow:Mo Reference Property
workflowMoReferenceProperty.description: Capture all the properties for an Intersight managed object reference.

DisplayAttributes.description: List of properties from an Intersight object which can help to identify the object. Typically the set of identity constraints on the object can be listed here to help the user identity the managed object.

Selector.description: Field to hold an Intersight API along with an optional filter to narrow down the search options.

ValueAttribute.description: A property from the Intersight object, value of which can be used as value for referenced input definition.

workflowPendingDynamicWorkflowInfo.title: Workflow:Pending Dynamic Workflow Info
workflowPendingDynamicWorkflowInfo.description: Information for a pending Dynamic Workflow Instance before it is run.  Validation needs to be done on the dynamic workflow tasks before starting.  After it begins, it will be tracked with regular WorkflowInstance.

Name.description: A name for the pending dynamic workflow.

PendingServices.description: The pending services the dynamic workflow is waiting for to return the task list.

Src.description: The src is workflow owner service.

Status.description: The current status of the PendingDynamicWorkflowInfo.

WaitOnDuplicate.description: When set to true workflow engine will wait for a duplicate to finish before starting a new one.

WorkflowActionTaskLists.description: The task lists returned by services for building dynamic workflows.  There will be an entry for every different workflow action.

WorkflowCtx.description: The workflow's workflow context which contains initiator and target information.

WorkflowKey.description: This key contains workflow, initiator and target name. Workflow engine uses the key to do workflow dedup.

WorkflowInfo.description:
A collection of references to the [workflow.WorkflowInfo](mo://workflow.WorkflowInfo) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [workflow.WorkflowInfo](mo://workflow.WorkflowInfo) MO unsets its reference to this deleted MO.

Count.description: The number of workflowPendingDynamicWorkflowInfos matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowPendingDynamicWorkflowInfos matching your request.

workflowPrimitiveArrayItem.title: Workflow:Primitive Array Item
workflowPrimitiveArrayItem.description: PrimitiveArrayItem is used to create an array of primitive datatype. In order to create an array of strings, integers or float use PrimitiveArrayItem object type within the array.

Properties.description: Captures an array item which is of primitive data type.

workflowPrimitiveDataProperty.title: Workflow:Primitive Data Property
workflowPrimitiveDataProperty.description: Capture all the properties for primitive data type.

Constraints.description: Constraints that must be applied to the parameter value supplied for this data type.

InventorySelector.description: List of Intersight managed object selectors. The workflow execution user interface show objects from inventory that are matching the selectors to help with selecting inputs.

Secure.description:
Intersight supports secure properties as task input/output. The values of
these properties are encrypted and stored in Intersight.
This flag marks the property to be secure when it is set to true.

Type.description: Specify the enum type for primitive data type.

workflowPrimitiveDataType.title: Workflow:Primitive Data Type
workflowPrimitiveDataType.description: This data type is used to represent primitives like string, floats and integers.

workflowProperties.title: Workflow:Properties
workflowProperties.description: Properties for the task definition like the inputs, outputs, timeout and retry policies. Tasks are the building blocks for workflows.

ExternalMeta.description: When set to false the task definition can only be used by internal system workflows. When set to true then the task can be included in user defined workflows.

InputDefinition.description: The schema expected for input parameters for this task.

OutputDefinition.description: The schema expected for output parameters for this task.

RetryCount.description: The number of times a task should be tried before marking as failed.

RetryDelay.description: The delay in seconds after which the the task is re-tried.

RetryPolicy.description: The retry policy for the task.

Timeout.description: The timeout value in seconds after which task will be marked as timed out. Max allowed value is 7 days.

TimeoutPolicy.description: The timeout policy for the task.

workflowStartTask.title: Workflow:Start Task
workflowStartTask.description: A StartTask is the starting point for a workflow.  There can only be one StartTask in a workflow.

NextTask.description: The name of the next task (Task names unique within workflow) to run.  In a graph model, denotes an edge to another Task Node.

workflowSubWorkflowTask.title: Workflow:Sub Workflow Task
workflowSubWorkflowTask.description: A SubWorkflowTask is used to include another workflow as a task within this workflow.

CatalogMoid.description: Specify the catalog moid that this task belongs.

Version.description: The workflow definition version to use as subworkflow. When no version is specified then the default version of the workflow at the time of creating or updating this workflow is used.

WorkflowDefinitionId.description: The resolved referenced workflow definition managed object.

WorkflowDefinitionName.description: The qualified name of workflow that should be executed as a task.

workflowSuccessEndTask.title: Workflow:Success End Task
workflowSuccessEndTask.description: A SuccessEndTask denotes the successful completion of a workflow.

workflowTargetDataType.title: Workflow:Target Data Type
workflowTargetDataType.description: Data type to capture a target endpoint or device.

Properties.description: Reference to target device or endpoint managed object.

workflowTargetProperty.title: Workflow:Target Property
workflowTargetProperty.description: Capture all the properties for an input target endpoint or device.

ConnectorAttribute.description: A singleton value which will contain the path to connector object from the selected object.

ConstraintAttributes.description: A collection of properties that will be used to match a specific implemented task. Using these values, the workflow engine will try to pick an implemented task definition when multiple implementations exist.

DisplayAttributes.description: List of properties from the Intersight object which can help to identify the object. Typically the set of identity constraints on the object can be listed here to help the user identity the managed object.

Selector.description: Field to hold an Intersight API along with an optional filter to narrow down the search options for target device.

SupportedObjects.description: An explicit set of concrete objectTypes supported as part of this property entry.

workflowTaskConstraints.title: Workflow:Task Constraints
workflowTaskConstraints.description: Captures the constraints for a task. Currently, it hold only targetDataType constraints such as Vendor, ObjectType that are properties of a target device.

TargetDataType.description: List of property constraints that helps to narrow down task implementations based on target device input.

workflowTaskDefinition.title: Workflow:Task Definition
workflowTaskDefinition.description: Used to define a task which can be included within a workflow. Task definition conveys the intent that we want to achieve with the task. We can have a standalone task definition that is bound to a single implementation for that task, or we can define an TaskDefinition that will serve as the interface task definition which is linked to multiple implementation tasks. Each implemented TaskDefinition will be bound to its own implementation so we can achieve a case where single TaskDefinition has multiple implementations.

DefaultVersion.description: When true this will be the task version that is used when a specific task definition version is not specified. The very first task definition created with a name will be set as the default version, after that user can explicitly set any version of the task definition as the default version.

Description.description: The task definition description to describe what this task will do when executed.

InternalProperties.description: Type to capture all the internal properties for the task definition.

Label.description: A user friendly short name to identify the task definition.

LicenseEntitlement.description: License entitlement required to run this task. It is determined by license requirement of features.

Name.description: The name of the task definition. The name should follow this convention <Verb or Action><Category><Vendor><Product><Noun or object> Verb or Action is a required portion of the name and this must be part of the pre-approved verb list. Category is an optional field and this will refer to the broad category of the task referring to the type of resource or endpoint. If there is no specific category then use "Generic" if required. Vendor is an optional field and this will refer to the specific vendor this task applies to. If the task is generic and not tied to a vendor, then do not specify anything. Product is an optional field, this will contain the vendor product and model when desired. Noun or object is a required field and  this will contain the noun or object on which the action is being performed. Examples SendEmail  - This is a task in Generic category for sending email. NewStorageVolume - This is a vendor agnostic task under Storage device category for creating a new volume.

Properties.description: Type to capture all the properties for the task definition.

SecurePropAccess.description: If set to true, the task requires access to secure properties and uses an encyption token associated with a workflow moid to encrypt or decrypt the secure properties.

Version.description: The version of the task definition so we can support multiple versions of a task definition.

Catalog.description: The catalog under which the definition has been added.

ImplementedTasks.description: List of all the implemented task for this TaskDefinition. When this list is populated it implies that this TaskDefinition has multiple implementations.

InterfaceTask.description:
A collection of references to the [workflow.TaskDefinition](mo://workflow.TaskDefinition) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [workflow.TaskDefinition](mo://workflow.TaskDefinition) MO unsets its reference to this deleted MO.

Count.description: The number of workflowTaskDefinitions matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowTaskDefinitions matching your request.

workflowTaskInfo.title: Workflow:Task Info
workflowTaskInfo.description: Task instance which represents the run time instance of a task within a workflow.

Description.description: The task description and this is the description that was added when the task was included into the workflow.

EndTime.description: The time stamp when the task reached a final state.

FailureReason.description: Description of the reason why the task failed.

Input.description: The input data that was sent to the task at the start of execution.

InstId.description: The current running task instance Id.

Internal.description: Denotes whether or not this is an internal task.  Internal tasks will be hidden from the UI within a workflow.

Label.description: User friendly short label to describe this task instance in the workflow.

Message.description: Collection of Task execution messages with severity.

Name.description: Task definition name which specifies the task type.

Output.description: The output data that was generated by this task.

RefName.description: The task reference name to ensure its unique inside a workflow.

RetryCount.description: A counter for number of retries.

StartTime.description: The time stamp when the task started execution.

Status.description: The status of the task and this will specify if the task is running or has reached a final state.

TaskInstIdList.description: The list keeps a list of retried task instances.

SubWorkflowInfo.description:
A collection of references to the [workflow.WorkflowInfo](mo://workflow.WorkflowInfo) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [workflow.WorkflowInfo](mo://workflow.WorkflowInfo) MO unsets its reference to this deleted MO.

TaskDefinition.description: The task definition that was used to launch this task execution instance.

WorkflowInfo.description:
A collection of references to the [workflow.WorkflowInfo](mo://workflow.WorkflowInfo) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [workflow.WorkflowInfo](mo://workflow.WorkflowInfo) MO unsets its reference to this deleted MO.

Count.description: The number of workflowTaskInfos matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowTaskInfos matching your request.

workflowTaskMeta.title: Workflow:Task Meta
workflowTaskMeta.description: This MO contains a task definition.

ActionType.description: A task execution type to indicate if it is a system task.

Description.description: A description of the task.

InputKeys.description: Input keys for the task which specifies parameters the task can take in as inputs.

Internal.description: Denotes whether or not this is an internal task.  Internal tasks will be hidden from the UI within a workflow.

Name.description: A task name that should be unique in Conductor DB.

OutputKeys.description: Output keys for the task which specifies parameters the task will output at the end of execution.

RetryCount.description: A number of reties for this task.

RetryDelaySec.description: The time on which the retry will be delayed.

RetryLogic.description: A logic which defines the way to handle retry (FIXED, EXPONENTIAL_BACKOFF).

Src.description: A service owns the task metadata.

TimeoutPolicy.description: A policy which defines the way to handle timeout (RETRY, TIME_OUT_WF, ALERT_ONLY).

TimeoutSec.description: A timeout value for the task in seconds.

Count.description: The number of workflowTaskMeta matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowTaskMeta matching your request.

workflowTaskRetryInfo.title: Workflow:Task Retry Info
workflowTaskRetryInfo.description: Keep track of task retry information using TaskRetryInfo.

Status.description: Status of the retried task.

TaskInstId.description: Retry instance will get a unique instance id.

workflowValidationError.title: Workflow:Validation Error
workflowValidationError.description: Used to show validation errors for the workflow or for the task within the workflow.

Field.description: When populated this refers to the input or output field within the workflow or task.

TaskName.description: The task name on which the error is found, when empty the error applies to the top level workflow.

TransitionName.description: When populated this refers to the transition connection that has a problem. When this field has value OnSuccess it means the transition connection OnSuccess for the task has an issue.

workflowValidationInformation.title: Workflow:Validation Information
workflowValidationInformation.description: Type used to capture all the validation information for the workflow definition.

State.description: The current validation state of this workflow. The possible states are Valid, Invalid, NotValidated (default).

ValidationError.description: List of all workflow or task validation errors. The validation errors can be for worker task or for control tasks.

workflowWaitTask.title: Workflow:Wait Task
workflowWaitTask.description: A WaitTask will remain in progress until marked success or failed by an external trigger. The timeout for wait task is 180 days, so a workflow can wait for task status update for upto 180 days. Currently the only supported means to update the task status is through an API that provides the status of the task runtime instance. Once the wait task status has been set the workflow will continue with the execution based on the task status.

Prompts.description: List of prompts for this wait task. These prompts are useful to provide options to the user who is running a workflow that contains wait task on how to proceed after the wait task.

workflowWaitTaskPrompt.title: Workflow:Wait Task Prompt
workflowWaitTaskPrompt.description: WaitTaskPrompt is used to create a customized prompts for wait control task. Wait task can be used in workflow for variety of reason, the prompts will help workflow designer to provide a customized set of prompts.

Description.description: Description that give more details about what it means to pick this prompt option for the wait task.

Label.description: User friendly label for the prompt. This label will be shown to the user as one of available options for the wait task.

Name.description: Name for the wait prompt.

TaskStatus.description: Task status for the wait task when this prompt option is selected.

workflowWebApi.title: Web API
workflowWebApi.description:
This models a single Web API request within a batch of requests that get
executed within a single workflow task.

EndpointRequestType.description:
If the target type is Endpoint, this property determines whether the request is
to be handled as internal request or external request by the device connector.

Headers.description: Collection of key value pairs to set in the request header.

Method.description:
The HTTP method to be executed in the given URL (GET, POST, PUT, etc).
If the value is not specified, GET will be used as default.

MoType.description:
The type of the intersight object for which API request is to be made.
The property is valid in case of Intersight API calls and the base url is automatically prepended based on the value.

Protocol.description: The accepted web protocol values are http and https.

TargetType.description:
If the web API is to be executed in a remote device connected to the
Intersight through device connector, 'Endpoint' is expected as the value
whereas if the API is an Intersight API, 'Local' is expected as the value.

Url.description: The URL of the resource in the target to which the API request is made.

workflowWorkerTask.title: Workflow:Worker Task
workflowWorkerTask.description: A WorkerTask is a simple task and the smallest granularity of work that can be defined as a task.

CatalogMoid.description: Specify the catalog moid that this task belongs.

TaskDefinitionId.description: The resolved referenced task definition managed object.

TaskDefinitionName.description: The qualified name of task that should be executed.

Version.description: The task definition version to use in this workflow. When no version is specified then the default version of the task at the time of creating or updating this workflow is used.

workflowWorkflowDefinition.title: Workflow Definition
workflowWorkflowDefinition.description: Workflow definition is a collection of tasks that are sequenced in a certain way using control tasks. The tasks in the workflow definition is represented as a directed acyclic graph where each node in the graph is a task and the edges in the graph are transitions from one task to another.

DefaultVersion.description: When true this will be the workflow version that is used when a specific workflow definition version is not specified. The default version is used when user executes a workflow without specifying a version or when workflow is included in another workflow without a specific version. The very first workflow definition created with a name will be set as the default version, after that user can explicitly set any version of the workflow definition as the default version.

Description.description: The description for this workflow.

InputDefinition.description: The schema expected for input parameters for this workflow.

Label.description: A user friendly short name to identify the workflow. Name can only contain letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), hyphen (-), period (.), colon (:), space ( ) or an underscore (_).

LicenseEntitlement.description: License entitlement required to run this workflow. It is calculated based on the highest license requirement of all its tasks.

MaxTaskCount.description: The maximum number of tasks that can be executed on this workflow.

Name.description: The name for this workflow. You can have multiple versions of the workflow with the same name. Name can only contain letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), hyphen (-), period (.), colon (:) or an underscore (_).

OutputDefinition.description: The schema expected for output parameters for this workflow.

OutputParameters.description: The output mappings for the workflow. The outputs for worflows will generally be task output variables that we want to export out at the end of the workflow. The format to specify the mapping is '${Source.output.JsonPath}'. 'Source' is the name of the task within the workflow. You can map any task output to a workflow output as long as the types are compatible. Following this is JSON path expression to extract JSON fragment from source's output.

Properties.description: Type to capture the properties of a workflow definition. Some of these properties are passed to workflow execution instance.

Tasks.description: The tasks contained inside of the workflow.

UiRenderingData.description: This will hold the data needed for workflow to be rendered in the user interface.

ValidationInformation.description: The current validation state and associated information for this workflow.

Version.description: The version of the workflow to support multiple versions.

Catalog.description: The catalog under which the definition is present.

Count.description: The number of workflowWorkflowDefinitions matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowWorkflowDefinitions matching your request.

workflowWorkflowInfo.title: Workflow:Workflow Info
workflowWorkflowInfo.description: Contains information for a workflow execution which is a runtime instance of workflow.

Action.description: The action of the workflow such as start, cancel, retry, pause.

CleanupTime.description: The time when the workflow info will be removed from database.

EndTime.description: The time when the workflow reached a final state.

FailedWorkflowCleanupDuration.description: The duration in hours after which the workflow info for failed, terminated or timed out workflow will be removed from database.

Input.description: All the given inputs for the workflow.

InstId.description: A workflow instance Id which is the unique identified for the workflow execution.

Internal.description: Denotes if this workflow is internal and should be hidden from user view of running workflows.

LastAction.description: The last action that was issued on the workflow is saved in this field.

Message.description: Collection of Workflow execution messages with severity.

MetaVersion.description: Version of the workflow metadata for which this workflow execution was started.

Name.description: A name of the workflow execution instance.

Output.description: All the generated outputs for the workflow.

Progress.description: This field indicates percentage of workflow task execution.

Properties.description: Type to capture all the properties for the workflow info passed on from workflow definition.

RetryFromTaskName.description: This field is applicable when Retry action is issued for a workflow which is in a final state. When this field is not specified then the workflow will retry from the start of the workflow. When this field is specified then the workflow will be retried from the specified task. The field should carry the task name which is the unique name of the task within the workflow. The task name must be one of the tasks that completed or failed in the previous run, you cannot retry a workflow from a task which wasn't run in the previous iteration.

Src.description: The source microservice name which is the owner for this workflow.

StartTime.description: The time when the workflow was started for execution.

Status.description: A status of the workflow (RUNNING, WAITING, COMPLETED, TIME_OUT, FAILED).

SuccessWorkflowCleanupDuration.description: The duration in hours after which the workflow info for successful workflow will be removed from database.

TraceId.description: The trace id to keep track of workflow execution.

Type.description: A type of the workflow (serverconfig, ansible_monitoring).

UserId.description: The user identifier which indicates the user that started this workflow.

WaitReason.description: Denotes the reason workflow is in waiting status.

WorkflowCtx.description: The workflow context which contains initiator and target information.

WorkflowMetaType.description: The type of workflow meta. Derived from the workflow meta that is used to launch this workflow instance.

WorkflowTaskCount.description: Total number of workflow tasks in this workflow.

_0_ClusterProfile.description:
A collection of references to the [hyperflex.ClusterProfile](mo://hyperflex.ClusterProfile) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [hyperflex.ClusterProfile](mo://hyperflex.ClusterProfile) MO unsets its reference to this deleted MO.

_1_Profile.description:
A collection of references to the [server.Profile](mo://server.Profile) Managed Object.
When this managed object is deleted, the referenced [server.Profile](mo://server.Profile) MO unsets its reference to this deleted MO.

Account.description: The Account to which the workflow is associated.

Organization.description: The Organization to which the workflow is associated.

ParentTaskInfo.description: Link to the task in the parent workflow which launched this workflow.

PendingDynamicWorkflowInfo.description: Reference to the PendingDynamicWorkflowInfo that was used to construct this workflow instance.

Permission.description: Reference to the permission object for which user has access to start this workflow.

TaskInfos.description: List of task instances that ran as part of this workflow execution.

WorkflowDefinition.description: The workflow definition that was used to launch this workflow execution instance.

Count.description: The number of workflowWorkflowInfos matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowWorkflowInfos matching your request.

Retryable.description: When true, this workflow can be retried if has not been modified for more than a period of 2 weeks.

workflowWorkflowMeta.title: Workflow:Workflow Meta
workflowWorkflowMeta.description: Contains a workflow definition which is a sequence of tasks to execute.

Description.description: The description for the workflow.

Name.description: The name given to the workflow.

Retryable.description: When true, this workflow can be retried for 2 weeks since the last modification of the workflow.

SchemaVersion.description: The Conductor schema version that decides what attribute can be supported.

Src.description: The src is workflow owner service.

Tasks.description: The tasks contained inside of the workflow.

Type.description: The type of workflow definition.

Version.description: The version for the workflow so we can support multiple versions for the same workflow name.

WaitOnDuplicate.description: Parameter decides if workflows will wait for a duplicate to finish before starting a new one.

Organization.description: Relationship to the Organization that owns the Managed Object.

Count.description: The number of workflowWorkflowMeta matching your request in total for all pages.

Results.description: The array of workflowWorkflowMeta matching your request.

ExternalMeta.description: When set to false the workflow is owned by the system and used for internal services. Such workflows cannot be directly used by external entities.

Retryable.description: When true, this workflow can be retried if has not been modified for more than a period of 2 weeks.

workflowWorkflowTask.title: Workflow:Workflow Task
workflowWorkflowTask.description: Task instance within the workflow to be executed.

Description.description: The description of this task instance in the workflow.

Label.description: A user defined label identifier of the workflow task used for UI display.

Name.description: The name of the task within the workflow and it must be unique among all WorkflowTasks within a workflow definition. This name serves as the internal unique identifier for the task and is used to pick input and output parameters to feed into other tasks.

workflowXmlApi.title: XML API
workflowXmlApi.description:
This models a single XML API request that can be sent to any Cisco UCS devices
that support Cisco UCS XML API interface.

x509Certificate.title: X509:Certificate
x509Certificate.description: The representation of an X.509 certificate.

Issuer.description: The X.509 distinguished name of the issuer of this certificate.

NotAfter.description: The date on which the certificate's validity period ends.

NotBefore.description: The date on which the certificate's validity period begins.

PemCertificate.description: The base64 encoded certificate in PEM format.

Sha256Fingerprint.description: The computed SHA-256 fingerprint of the certificate. Equivalent to 'openssl x509 -fingerprint -sha256'.

Subject.description: The X.509 distinguished name of the subject of this certificate.

messageId.description: A language-independent identifier of the specific error.
